                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="61421" author="fuzzylogic" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2005 03:38:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you check out and build Derby yourself, the default mode of building is a debug build. See the sections about the &apos;sane&apos; build property in BUILDING.txt here:  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/incubator/derby/code/trunk/BUILDING.txt?rev=157009&amp;amp;view=markup&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewcvs.cgi/incubator/derby/code/trunk/BUILDING.txt?rev=157009&amp;amp;view=markup&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With the consideration that products embedding Derby would desire a jar file with as small a footprint as possible, I created the distributions on the website with an insane/non-debug build, with all compiler optimizations turned on and assertions removed. However, perhaps posting a -debug distribution along with the -lib, -bin, and -src distributions should be considered.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12329328" author="jfrantzius" created="Thu, 15 Sep 2005 03:52:14 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A -debug distribution would be really great. I just stepped in to issue #151 and it would be nice to quickly have a look in the source code what is going on. People would be enabled to provide more information on issues they find.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you could create an Eclipse plugin with source and -debug classes, now that would be really absolutely great &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The Eclipse plugin doesn&apos;t need to have a small footprint anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12377800" author="jfrantzius" created="Thu, 4 May 2006 20:47:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Again I&apos;m having big difficulties to debug Derby to find out what the original IOException is for &quot;ERROR XSDG3: Meta-data for Container org.apache.derby.impl.store.raw.data.RAFContainer@110e392 could not be accessed&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Not having proper line information in the class files is a BIG hindrance, and building Derby myself again will be a time-consuming task. This is really the only Java OSS I have seen that does not include line information.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe the additional debug-distribution could be more than considered? This will make it easier for users to provide detailed information e.g. in bug reports.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12378791" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 10 May 2006 08:58:13 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Added debug snapshots as of the 10.1.2.4 snapshot posted. I&apos;ll add a debug-lib distribution for the 10.1.3 and future releases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12378838" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 10 May 2006 15:05:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;With revisions 405655 and 405656, added targets to tools/release so that future official releases of Derby include a lib-debug distribution containing jars built with line number tables and non-optimized for easy use in debugging.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Marking this Resolved. Jorg, please close this if the lib-debug distributions in the upcoming 10.1.3 release in June satisfy this requirement to your satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
andrew&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12435145" author="rhillegas" created="Sat, 16 Sep 2006 00:03:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Toggling off the &quot;release note needed&quot; flag since this release note went into 10.1.3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12551270" author="fuzzylogic" created="Thu, 13 Dec 2007 09:04:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue has been resolved for over a year with no further movement. Closing.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
